<font color="#FF0000">IN PROCESSING</font><br>
<tt>Sat Apr 26  6:56:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
O.K., the sun is up and it is morning here in the Shenandoah Valley.  I've got to go cut my acreage (1.5) and process these last couple days of posts.<br>
There is obviously a sense of outrage and concern going on here.  One of the unique things about the site is that all posts are in black and white.  Seems strange that race has become an issue. It wasn't invited into our mishmash of problems, but sometimes the world intrudes into our reflections.  I think that as much as we would like to be insulated from the outside to solve our concerns; we occasionally get slapped with a dose of reality.<br>
Trollers, racists, vets with attitudes are going to be on this site.  It is open for any comments.  I felt personally attacked when I got the mail from Doc.  I cannot abide bigotry and any b.s. that cloaks it.  What may have happened was the frustration of the site closing caused folks to go out in a blaze.  But it still doesn't justify those attacks.<br>
Barry, you amaze me.  You keep throwing new things into the mix.  You are like an onion that has so many layers that I wonder if we will ever see the core.<br>
John, good to see you posting again.  I missed you r stuff. I got to the meat of things quickly.<br>
What I miss is the responses of Art, the Wingman, and Tanker.  These guys usually put things in focus.  Maybe the shock hit too hard.<br>
Strange how when we have so many things to say that the forum shifts to cloud the reasoning.<br>
But I ramble.  I have processing to do.  Later.
<p><code>-- cbotkins@visuallink.com  (Chet Botkins) </code><p>


